{
  "name": "8-Inner Gates: Shimon",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/7th-inner-gate.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Category</strong>: Taijutsu, Rare</p><p><strong>Prerequisite</strong>: 8-Inner Gates: Keimon, Taijutsu Ability Score of 20+, Level 16+</p><hr /><p>You have become a master of the Eight Inner Gates, unlocking the final 2 gates; Kyomon and Shimon You must currently be gaining the benefit of Keimon, in order to activate Kyomon.</p><p>You must complete a rest to gain the benefit of any Gate granted by this feat a second time.</p><p>If you would attempt to gain the benefit of a Gate granted by this feat a second time without taking a rest, you instead must spend 2 hit die to do so, which are not recovered until you complete a full-rest.</p><p>When you would end the activation of or be forced to end any 8-Inner gate, you gain all Ranks of any Fatigue and Weakened listed.</p><p>After ending any gate granted by this feature, you lose one rank of Fatigue every 24 hours;</p><ul><li><p>Kyomon.</p><ul><li><p>Str: +6</p></li><li><p>AC: +1</p></li><li><p>+2 Rank of Fatigue</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Shimon.</p><ul><li><p>Str: +6</p></li><li><p>Con: +2</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Triple Speed.</p><ul><li><p>AC: +2 o Extra Action.</p></li><li><p>You die, slowly turning to dust, which cannot be stopped or prevented. You become unable to be revived by any means.</p></li></ul></li></ul><img src=\"systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Cheat%20Sheet/Fatigue%20Chart.png\" /><p></p>",
